Step 1: Calculate the Current Ratio using the ending balance amounts from the balance sheet.
• Total Current Assets (end) = 21,224,639.20
• Total Current Liabilities (end) = 727,140.68
• Current Ratio = 21,224,639.20 / 727,140.68 ≈ 29.19

Step 2: Calculate the Inventory Turnover Ratio.
The formula used is:
 Inventory Turnover Ratio = Cost of Goods Sold / Average Inventory
Since the beginning Inventory is 0 and the ending Inventory is 8,400,000.00, then:
• Average Inventory = (0 + 8,400,000.00) / 2 = 4,200,000.00
• Cost of Goods Sold = 10,400,000.00
• Inventory Turnover Ratio = 10,400,000.00 / 4,200,000.00 ≈ 2.48

Final Answer in the required JSON format:
{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "29.19",
    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "2.48"
  }
}
